title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 64 Carbine 30 WCF Lyman 56 1935
postcontent: Offered for your consideration is a fine early model 64 carbine made in 1935. Factory correct 20 inch carbine barrel with integral front sight ramp, bore is sharp and mirror bright. The barrell and magazine retain 95% original blue. The receiver is mechanically fine, feeds, fires and ejects smoothly. Headspace is perfect. Receiver has the typical mottled finish from this era, the carbona blue just never held that well on the nickle steel Winchester used in the receivers. It has the Lyman 56 receiver sight which was a factory option. The wood is solid and tight, nicely grained black walnut that has a few very minor handling marks but no chips, cracks, extra holes or bad dents. This is a fine vintage Winchester that has that "slick as glass" feel when you cycle the bolt. A rare model 64 factory carbine from an era of fine craftmanship we will probably never see again.

The MAS-49 semi-automatic rifle was produced in limited quantities.
